toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3775</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00ME</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00ME.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Enumerable set</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A set <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>enumerable</fr:strong></fr:em> whenever there exists a surjection <fr:tex>\mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A</fr:tex>, referred to as an <fr:em><fr:strong>enumeration</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>In an <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumeration</fr:link> <fr:tex>e \colon   \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A</fr:tex> of a set <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>, we think of <fr:tex>n \in \mathbb {N}</fr:tex> as a “code” for <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex> when <fr:tex>e { \mathopen {} \left ( n \right ) \mathclose {}} =a</fr:tex>; these “codes” are not unique unless <fr:tex>e</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KR">bijection</fr:link>. By virtue of the viewpoint of quotients as surjections developed in <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MB"
href="jms-00MB.xml"
taxon="Example"></fr:ref>, <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerability</fr:link> expresses when a given set can be built up from the natural numbers by quotienting (i.e. identifying codes that are taken to the same element by the <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumeration</fr:link>).</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3778</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00MH</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MH.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Countable set</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>countable set</fr:strong></fr:em> is one that is either empty or <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3783</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00MI</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MI.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Alternative definition of <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countability</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A set <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable</fr:link> if and only if the disjoint union <fr:tex>A+ { \mathopen {} \left  [ 1 \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3781</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#385</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-385.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MI</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Suppose that <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable</fr:link>. We must find a <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A+ { \mathopen {} \left  [ 1 \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>; if <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is empty, this is the same as to find a <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathbb {N} \to { \mathopen {} \left  [ 1 \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, which we have by <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MA"
href="jms-00MA.xml"
taxon="Example"></fr:ref>. On the other hand, if we have an enumeration <fr:tex>e \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow {A}</fr:tex>, we may define an enumeration <fr:tex>e' \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A+ { \mathopen {} \left  [ 1 \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">    \begin {aligned}   e' { \mathopen {} \left ( 0 \right ) \mathclose {}}  &amp;= 0 \\    e' { \mathopen {} \left ( n+1 \right ) \mathclose {}}  &amp;= e { \mathopen {} \left ( n \right ) \mathclose {}}     \end {aligned}  </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Conversely, suppose that <fr:tex>A+ { \mathopen {} \left  [ 1 \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link> by <fr:tex>e \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A+ { \mathopen {} \left  [ 1 \right  ] \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>. If <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is empty, we are done. If to the contrary <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is inhabited by some <fr:tex>a_0</fr:tex>, we let define <fr:tex>e' \colon   \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A</fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">   e' { \mathopen {} \left ( i \right ) \mathclose {}}  =    \begin {cases}    e { \mathopen {} \left ( i \right ) \mathclose {}}  &amp; \text {when } e { \mathopen {} \left ( i \right ) \mathclose {}} \in  A \\     a_0 &amp; \text {otherwise}    \end {cases}  </fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3785</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00MJ</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MJ.xml</fr:route><fr:title>A <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KR">bijective</fr:link> enumeration of the integers</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We can define a bijective enumeration of the integers by “zigzagging” between the positive and the negative following the pattern<fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( 0, -1, 1,-2,2,-3,3, \ldots \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \begin {aligned}   e&amp; \colon   \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow   \mathbb {Z} \\    e { \mathopen {} \left ( i \right ) \mathclose {}}  &amp;=    \begin {cases}    0 &amp; \text {when } i=0 \\     i \div  2 &amp; \text {when } i &gt; 0  \land  2 \mid  i \\     - { \mathopen {} \left ( i+1 \right ) \mathclose {}} \div  2 &amp; \text {when } i &gt; 0  \land   \lnot { \mathopen {} \left ( 2 \mid  i \right ) \mathclose {}}     \end {cases}   \end {aligned} </fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3790</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00MK</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MK.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Non-empty subsets of <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link> sets are <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Any non-empty subset of an <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link> set is <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3788</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#384</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-384.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MK</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We will use the same method as in our proof of <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MI"
href="jms-00MI.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>S \subseteq  A</fr:tex> be a non-empty subset of an <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerable</fr:link> set <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>, so that we have some <fr:tex>s \in  S</fr:tex> and a <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex>e \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A</fr:tex>. We define <fr:tex>e' \colon   \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow {S}</fr:tex> to send <fr:tex>i \in \mathbb {N}</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>e { \mathopen {} \left ( i \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> if <fr:tex>e { \mathopen {} \left ( i \right ) \mathclose {}} \in  S</fr:tex> and to <fr:tex>s</fr:tex> otherwise.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3795</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00ML</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00ML.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Cartesian product of <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable sets</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The cartesian product of <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable</fr:link> sets is <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3793</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#383</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-383.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00ML</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> be <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable</fr:link> sets. If either <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> or <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> is empty, then <fr:tex>A \times  B</fr:tex> is empty and thus <fr:link
href="jms-00MH.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MH">countable</fr:link>. Otherwise, let <fr:tex>e_A \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>e_B \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  B</fr:tex> be <fr:link
href="jms-00ME.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00ME">enumerations</fr:link> of <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> respectively. Then the function <fr:tex>e_A \times  e_B \colon   \mathbb {N} \times \mathbb {N} \to  A \times  B</fr:tex> can be seen to be <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link>; letting <fr:tex>f \colon   \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow \mathbb {N} \times \mathbb {N}</fr:tex> be any enumeration of <fr:tex>\mathbb {N} \times \mathbb {N}</fr:tex>, can compose to obtain a surjection <fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( e_A \times  e_B \right ) \mathclose {}} \circ  f \colon \mathbb {N} \twoheadrightarrow  A \times  B</fr:tex> by <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MD"
href="jms-00MD.xml"
taxon="Theorem"></fr:ref>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks><fr:tree
